\subsubsection{Chiral structure}

\com{Needed to properly describe this model simplification:  complete chiral structure in equation~\eqref{eq:lagrangianResonant} and~\eqref{eq:lagrangianNonResonantVector}}
 
The main point here is to consider only right handed quark components in order to not simplify the phenomenology. In fact, the representation of the left-handed 
components under the $\SUtwo$ symmetry impose a couplings to $down$-type quarks, since the effective theory is invariant under $\SUtwoUone$ gauge symmetry). Having a coupling between
the mediator and $down$-type quarks fairly complicates the collider phenomenology in term of decay mode. Typically, including the left-handed components of quarks in the lagrangian~\eqref{eq:lagrangianNonResonantVector} describing the $Vtu$ vertex would lead to  \com{Choose good notation of the couplings}
\begin{equation}
 \Lagr_{Vtu} \; = \; g_{R} \: \bar{t}_{R}\gam^{\mu}u_R \: V_{\mu} \; + \; g_{L} \left(   \bar{t}_{L}\gam^{\mu}u_L \: + \:  \bar{b}_{L}\gam^{\mu}d_L \right) \: V_{\mu}
\end{equation}
where the second term ensure the invariance under $\SUtwo$ rotations, and lead to an additional decay mode $V \to b\bar{d} + \bar{b}d$ (on top of $V \to t\bar{u} + \bar{t}u$ and $V \to \chi\chi$). 
 
