\section{Collider signatures}
\label{sec:ColliderSignature}
 
 As explained in the section~\ref{sec:MotivModelDescription}, there are two types of models that can be constrainted the following signatures at the LHC:
 \begin{enumerate}
  \item $t+\met$ final state (resonant and non-resonant production)
  \item $tt$ final state (non-resonant production)
 \end{enumerate}
 These two productions are highly suppressed in the SM and makes these channels good candidates to search for new physics. In the current section, details about the global search strategy are given in each cases and the interplay between the two final state is described. Finally, some considerations on pratical aspects are discussed, such as paramters scan or PDF and showering modeling for the signal generation.
 
